	     Durban - A woman is in a critical condition after she
stopped breathing when she came to the surface while scuba diving in Umhlanga
on Sunday morning, paramedics said. "Reports from the scene indicate that the diver was at
18 metres off Grannies pool in Umhlanga, she surfaced after doing decompression
stops and when she got to the surface she stopped breathing," said
Netcare911 spokesperson Chris Botha. "Netcare 911 paramedics arrived at the scene and found
the lifeguards doing CPR. The advanced life support paramedics placed the lady
on a ventilator and continued with resuscitation. After extensive effort medics
managed to regain the patient's heartbeat." She was admitted to a local hospital in Umhlanga. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  